#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.67"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.67:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.67:0.2"
msgid "7. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "7. The Great Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.67:0.3"
msgid "67. Kathāvatthusutta"
msgstr "67. Topics of Discussion"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.67:1.1"
msgid "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, kathāvatthūni."
msgstr "“There are, mendicants, these three topics of discussion."

msgctxt "an3.67:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.67:1.3"
msgid "Atītaṃ vā, bhikkhave, addhānaṃ ārabbha kathaṃ katheyya:"
msgstr "You might discuss the past:"

msgctxt "an3.67:1.4"
msgid "‘evaṃ ahosi atītamaddhānan’ti."
msgstr "‘That is how it was in the past.’"

msgctxt "an3.67:1.5"
msgid "Anāgataṃ vā, bhikkhave, addhānaṃ ārabbha kathaṃ katheyya:"
msgstr "You might discuss the future:"

msgctxt "an3.67:1.6"
msgid "‘evaṃ bhavissati anāgatamaddhānan’ti."
msgstr "‘That is how it will be in the future.’"

msgctxt "an3.67:1.7"
msgid "Etarahi vā, bhikkhave, paccuppannaṃ addhānaṃ ārabbha kathaṃ katheyya:"
msgstr "Or you might discuss the present:"

#. VAR: evaṃ hoti etarahi paccuppannamaddhānan’ti → evaṃ etarahi paccuppannanti (bj, pts1, mr) | evaṃ hoti etarahi paccuppannanti (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an3.67:1.8"
msgid "‘evaṃ hoti etarahi paccuppannamaddhānan’ti."
msgstr "‘This is how it is at present.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.67:2.1"
msgid ""
"Kathāsampayogena, bhikkhave, puggalo veditabbo yadi vā kaccho yadi vā "
"akacchoti."
msgstr ""
"You can know whether or not a person is competent to hold a discussion by "
"seeing how they take part in a discussion."

#. VAR: ṭhapanīyaṃ pañhaṃ na ṭhapeti → thapanīyaṃ pañhaṃ na thapeti (mr)
msgctxt "an3.67:2.2"
msgid ""
"Sacāyaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalo pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno ekaṃsabyākaraṇīyaṃ pañhaṃ "
"na ekaṃsena byākaroti, vibhajjabyākaraṇīyaṃ pañhaṃ na vibhajja byākaroti, "
"paṭipucchābyākaraṇīyaṃ pañhaṃ na paṭipucchā byākaroti, ṭhapanīyaṃ pañhaṃ na "
"ṭhapeti, evaṃ santāyaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalo akaccho hoti."
msgstr ""
"When a person is asked a question, if it needs to be answered with a "
"generalization and they don’t answer it generally; or if it needs analysis "
"and they answer without analyzing it; or if it needs a counter-question and "
"they answer without a counter-question; or if it should be set aside and "
"they don’t set it aside, then that person is not competent to hold a "
"discussion."

msgctxt "an3.67:2.3"
msgid ""
"Sace panāyaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalo pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno ekaṃsabyākaraṇīyaṃ "
"pañhaṃ ekaṃsena byākaroti, vibhajjabyākaraṇīyaṃ pañhaṃ vibhajja byākaroti, "
"paṭipucchābyākaraṇīyaṃ pañhaṃ paṭipucchā byākaroti, ṭhapanīyaṃ pañhaṃ "
"ṭhapeti, evaṃ santāyaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalo kaccho hoti."
msgstr ""
"When a person is asked a question, if it needs to be answered with a "
"generalization and they answer it generally; or if it needs analysis and "
"they answer after analyzing it; or if it needs a counter-question and they "
"answer with a counter-question; or if it should be set aside and they set it "
"aside, then that person is competent to hold a discussion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.198"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.67:3.1"
msgid ""
"Kathāsampayogena, bhikkhave, puggalo veditabbo yadi vā kaccho yadi vā "
"akacchoti."
msgstr ""
"You can know whether or not a person is competent to hold a discussion by "
"seeing how they take part in a discussion."

#. VAR: aññātavāde → aññavāde (bj, s1-3, km, pts1) | aññātavāre (mr)
msgctxt "an3.67:3.2"
msgid ""
"Sacāyaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalo pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno ṭhānāṭhāne na saṇṭhāti "
"parikappe na saṇṭhāti aññātavāde na saṇṭhāti paṭipadāya na saṇṭhāti, evaṃ "
"santāyaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalo akaccho hoti."
msgstr ""
"When a person is asked a question, if they’re not consistent about what "
"their position is and what it isn’t; about what they propose; about speaking "
"from what they know; and about the appropriate procedure, then that person "
"is not competent to hold a discussion."

msgctxt "an3.67:3.3"
msgid ""
"Sace panāyaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalo pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno ṭhānāṭhāne saṇṭhāti "
"parikappe saṇṭhāti aññātavāde saṇṭhāti paṭipadāya saṇṭhāti, evaṃ santāyaṃ, "
"bhikkhave, puggalo kaccho hoti."
msgstr ""
"When a person is asked a question, if they are consistent about what their "
"position is and what it isn’t; about what they propose; about speaking from "
"what they know; and about the appropriate procedure, then that person is "
"competent to hold a discussion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.67:4.1"
msgid ""
"Kathāsampayogena, bhikkhave, puggalo veditabbo yadi vā kaccho yadi vā "
"akacchoti."
msgstr ""
"You can know whether or not a person is competent to hold a discussion by "
"seeing how they take part in a discussion."

msgctxt "an3.67:4.2"
msgid ""
"Sacāyaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalo pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati, "
"bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeti, kopañca dosañca appaccayañca pātukaroti, evaṃ "
"santāyaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalo akaccho hoti."
msgstr ""
"When a person is asked a question, if they dodge the issue; distract the "
"discussion with irrelevant points; or display irritation, hate, and "
"bitterness, then that person is not competent to hold a discussion."

msgctxt "an3.67:4.3"
msgid ""
"Sace panāyaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalo pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno na aññenaññaṃ "
"paṭicarati na bahiddhā kathaṃ apanāmeti, na kopañca dosañca appaccayañca "
"pātukaroti, evaṃ santāyaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalo kaccho hoti."
msgstr ""
"When a person is asked a question, if they don’t dodge the issue; distract "
"the discussion with irrelevant points; or display irritation, hate, and "
"bitterness, then that person is competent to hold a discussion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.67:5.1"
msgid ""
"Kathāsampayogena, bhikkhave, puggalo veditabbo yadi vā kaccho yadi vā "
"akacchoti."
msgstr ""
"You can know whether or not a person is competent to hold a discussion by "
"seeing how they take part in a discussion."

#. VAR: anupajagghati → anusaṃjagghati (mr)
msgctxt "an3.67:5.2"
msgid ""
"Sacāyaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalo pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno abhiharati abhimaddati "
"anupajagghati khalitaṃ gaṇhāti, evaṃ santāyaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalo akaccho "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"When a person is asked a question, if they intimidate, crush, mock, or seize "
"on trivial mistakes, then that person is not competent to hold a discussion."

msgctxt "an3.67:5.3"
msgid ""
"Sace panāyaṃ, bhikkhave, puggalo pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno nābhiharati "
"nābhimaddati na anupajagghati na khalitaṃ gaṇhāti, evaṃ santāyaṃ, bhikkhave, "
"puggalo kaccho hoti."
msgstr ""
"When a person is asked a question, if they don’t intimidate, crush, mock, or "
"seize on trivial mistakes, then that person is competent to hold a "
"discussion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an3.67:6.1"
msgid ""
"Kathāsampayogena, bhikkhave, puggalo veditabbo yadi vā saupaniso yadi vā "
"anupanisoti."
msgstr ""
"You can know whether or not a person has what’s required by seeing how they "
"take part in a discussion."

msgctxt "an3.67:6.2"
msgid "Anohitasoto, bhikkhave, anupaniso hoti, ohitasoto saupaniso hoti."
msgstr ""
"If they lend an ear they have what’s required; if they don’t lend an ear "
"they don’t have what’s required."

msgctxt "an3.67:6.3"
msgid ""
"So saupaniso samāno abhijānāti ekaṃ dhammaṃ, parijānāti ekaṃ dhammaṃ, "
"pajahati ekaṃ dhammaṃ, sacchikaroti ekaṃ dhammaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Someone who has what’s required has insight into one thing, completely "
"understands one thing, gives up one thing, and realizes one thing—"

msgctxt "an3.67:6.4"
msgid ""
"So abhijānanto ekaṃ dhammaṃ, parijānanto ekaṃ dhammaṃ, pajahanto ekaṃ "
"dhammaṃ, sacchikaronto ekaṃ dhammaṃ sammāvimuttiṃ phusati."
msgstr "and then they experience complete freedom."

msgctxt "an3.67:6.5"
msgid "Etadatthā, bhikkhave, kathā;"
msgstr "This is the purpose of discussion,"

msgctxt "an3.67:6.6"
msgid "etadatthā mantanā;"
msgstr "consultation,"

msgctxt "an3.67:6.7"
msgid "etadatthā upanisā;"
msgstr "the requirements,"

msgctxt "an3.67:6.8"
msgid "etadatthaṃ sotāvadhānaṃ, yadidaṃ anupādā cittassa vimokkhoti."
msgstr ""
"and listening well, that is, the liberation of the mind by not grasping.”"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.199"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an3.67:7.1"
msgid "Ye viruddhā sallapanti,"
msgstr "“Those who converse with hostility,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:7.2"
msgid "viniviṭṭhā samussitā;"
msgstr "too sure of themselves, arrogant,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:7.3"
msgid "Anariyaguṇamāsajja,"
msgstr "ignoble, attacking virtues,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:7.4"
msgid "aññoññavivaresino."
msgstr "they look for flaws in each other."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an3.67:8.1"
msgid "Dubbhāsitaṃ vikkhalitaṃ,"
msgstr "They rejoice together when their opponent"

#. <br>
#. VAR: sampamohaṃ → sasammohaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an3.67:8.2"
msgid "sampamohaṃ parājayaṃ;"
msgstr "speaks poorly and makes a mistake,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:8.3"
msgid "Aññoññassābhinandanti,"
msgstr "becoming confused and defeated—"

#. <br>
#. VAR: tadariyo kathanācare → tadariyo na kathaṃ vade (mr)
msgctxt "an3.67:8.4"
msgid "tadariyo kathanācare."
msgstr "but the noble ones don’t discuss like this."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an3.67:9.1"
msgid "Sace cassa kathākāmo,"
msgstr "If an astute person wants to hold a discussion"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:9.2"
msgid "kālamaññāya paṇḍito;"
msgstr "connected with the teaching and its meaning—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:9.3"
msgid "Dhammaṭṭhapaṭisaṃyuttā,"
msgstr "the kind of discussion that noble ones hold—"

#. <br>
#. VAR: ariyacaritā → ariyācaritā (bj) | ariyañcaritā (si) | ariyādikā (mr)
msgctxt "an3.67:9.4"
msgid "yā ariyacaritā kathā."
msgstr "then that wise one should start the discussion,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an3.67:10.1"
msgid "Taṃ kathaṃ kathaye dhīro,"
msgstr "knowing when the time is right,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:10.2"
msgid "aviruddho anussito;"
msgstr "neither hostile nor arrogant."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:10.3"
msgid "Anunnatena manasā,"
msgstr "Not over-excited,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:10.4"
msgid "apaḷāso asāhaso."
msgstr "contemptuous, or aggressive,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
#. VAR: Anusūyāyamāno → anusuyyāyamāno (bj) | anusuyyamāno (s1-3)
msgctxt "an3.67:11.1"
msgid "Anusūyāyamāno so,"
msgstr "or with a mind full of jealousy,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:11.2"
msgid "sammadaññāya bhāsati;"
msgstr "they’d speak from what they rightly know."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:11.3"
msgid "Subhāsitaṃ anumodeyya,"
msgstr "They agree with what was well spoken,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: nāpasādaye → nāvasādaye (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.67:11.4"
msgid "dubbhaṭṭhe nāpasādaye."
msgstr "without criticizing what was poorly said."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an3.67:12.1"
msgid "Upārambhaṃ na sikkheyya,"
msgstr "They’d not persist in finding faults,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: na gāhaye → na bhāsaye (mr)
msgctxt "an3.67:12.2"
msgid "khalitañca na gāhaye;"
msgstr "nor seize on trivial mistakes,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:12.3"
msgid "Nābhihare nābhimadde,"
msgstr "neither intimidating nor crushing the other,"

# BB has mendacious for payuta, I’m not sure why. The word is obscure, but the comm connects it with the idea of dropping hints and suggestions; see entry in PTS dict.
#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:12.4"
msgid "na vācaṃ payutaṃ bhaṇe."
msgstr "nor would they speak with sly implications."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an3.67:13.1"
msgid "Aññātatthaṃ pasādatthaṃ,"
msgstr "Good people consult"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:13.2"
msgid "sataṃ ve hoti mantanā;"
msgstr "for the sake of knowledge and clarity."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:13.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho ariyā mantenti,"
msgstr "That’s how the noble ones consult,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:13.4"
msgid "esā ariyāna mantanā;"
msgstr "this is a noble consultation."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:13.5"
msgid "Etadaññāya medhāvī,"
msgstr "Knowing this, an intelligent person"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.67:13.6"
msgid "na samusseyya mantaye”ti."
msgstr "would consult without arrogance.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.67:13.7"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
